to expire at midnight EST Monday, but <ORGANIZATION> KKR </ORGANIZATION> late Friday extended its offer to 10 a.m. EST Thursday. The second step of the merger process, involving the exchange of securities not tendered to <ORGANIZATION> KKR </ORGANIZATION>, must still occur and there is no time limit for completion of that portion of the deal. Under an agreement between the <ORGANIZATION> FTC </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roberts </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> KKR </ORGANIZATION> must maintain <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> as a separate operation until the three product lines are sold. Before divestitures, the merged company would control about 12 -LCB- percent to 13 percent of the market for manufactured foods, said <PERSON> Jeffrey </PERSON> <PERSON> Zuckerman </PERSON>, head of the commission's <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Competition </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Zuckerman </PERSON> declined to give estimates of market share held by each of the lines but did give these estimates if the brands were combined: <PERSON> Chun </PERSON> <PERSON> King-La </PERSON> <PERSON> Choy </PERSON>, `` probably slightly under 60 percent'' of $ 300 million in sales; Del Monte-Hunt ketchup, about 25 percent of $ 500 million; and Planters-Fisher nuts, `` about 50 percent'' of $ 1.5 billion. Although market share is a concern, `` we look at other factors, the most important of which is the ease with which other people could enter the business'' if the company tried to raise prices, he said.
