Iraq </LOCATION> on Saturday. Before departing he told reporters: `` I leave with the impression that the release of <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Keenan </PERSON> before long remains a distinct possibility.'' <PERSON> Keenan </PERSON>, a teacher from <LOCATION> Belfast </LOCATION>, was kidnapped April 11, 1986 in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>'s Moslem sector. No group has claimed his abduction. <PERSON> McCabe </PERSON> said he would return to <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> `` in coming weeks or sooner'' if necessary.
