<BYLINE>By DONNA CASSATA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Tower </PERSON>'s reputation and the intent of the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Armed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> to conduct a thorough investigation collided head-on this week as the expected confirmation of the defense secretary-designate hit a snag. New allegations surfaced Thursday of a drinking problem and womanizing, prompting the committee to postpone a planned vote on Tower's nomination until the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> could complete a new inquiry. Despite the new twist to the well-circulated but unsubstantiated rumors, senators said they expect the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> panel to approve the Tower nomination and forward their recommendation to the full <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>. Sen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Warner </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>, ranking Republican on the panel, said he expected the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> report to reach the panel on Monday, `` and ... we can proceed to vote Tuesday or Wednesday.'' Tower was dogged by allegations of drinking and womanizing before his nomination. In divorce papers filed two years ago by his second wife, <PERSON> Lilla </PERSON> <PERSON> Burt </PERSON> <PERSON> Cummings </PERSON>, Tower was accused of `` marital misconduct.'' When President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> announced Tower's appointment, he said an <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> background check found nothing that would prevent Tower from serving as defense secretary. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> dismissed `` a lot of rumors that proved to be groundless.'' The ranking members of the committee, Sen. <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> <PERSON> Nunn </PERSON>, D-Ga., and <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION>, read the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> report, and any questions about Tower's personal life were reserved for executive sessions with committee But when conser