<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s leading dissident, <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> <PERSON> Lizhi </PERSON>, took his message straight to the establishment Saturday by telling a party attended by hundreds of actors, scientists, and businessmen they should work for human rights. `` Some people think <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> does n't need democracy, but I think human rights is basic,'' <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> said in a strong voice. Until his speech, the tea party had been non-political with some guests volunteering songs and stories. `` For -LRB- human rights -RRB- to be realized, first of all famous people must take a stand,'' he told the audience, which included many local leaders in the arts, science and trade. <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> and several other leading intellectuals were expelled from the <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> in 1987 after nationwide student demonstrations for democracy. More recently, authorities punished <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> for his outspokenness by revoking his permission to spend six months this year at the <ORGANIZATION> Colorado </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Joint </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Laboratory </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Astrophysics </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Fang </PERSON>, who is also known for his work as an astrophysicist, has made many pro-democracy speech to groups of sympathizers, particularly students. However, Saturday was the first time he took his message of democracy and human rights to an establishment audience. The party at a local hotel was organized by the <ORGANIZATION> Chinese </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cultural </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Academy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Academy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sciences </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ' </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entrepreneurial </ORGANIZA