ing </ORGANIZATION> also acknowledged this week that it had put decals mislabeling wiring connectors on 10 737-300s and -400 s that had been delivered to customers in December and January <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Craig </PERSON> <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> said none of those planes had actually been miswired or had connections improperly made. He said new decals were sent to the airlines.
