 Here are some commodity price trends for the past week: Grain and soybean futures had a mixed week on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION>. Wheat for delivery in March settled Friday at $ 4.30 \ a bushel, down from $ 4.40 -LCB- a week earlier; March corn was unchanged at $ 2.71 -RCB- a bushel; March oats advanced to $ 2.18 -RCB- a bushel from $ 2.12; and March soybeans rallied to $ 7.70 -LCB- a bushel from $ 7.54 Livestock and meat futures advanced on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. February live cattle improved to 75.55 cents a pound from 73.40 cents; March feeder cattle rose to 84.65 cents a pound from 83.17; February live hogs rallied to 44.02 cents a pound from 42.32 cents; and February frozen pork bellies advanced to 40.82 cents a pound from 38.60 cents. Gold and silver futures retreated for a second straight week on <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Commodity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. April gold settled Friday at $ 396.30 a troy ounce compared with $ 400.20 a week earlier; March silver fell to $ 5.875 from $ 6.245. Heating oil futures advanced but crude oil and gasoline slumped on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. West Texas Intermediate crude oil for March delivery fell to $ 17.53 a barrel from $ 17.74; heating oil rose to 50.31 cents a gallon from 49.88 cents; and March unleaded gasoline fell to 49.17 cents a gallon from 49.66 cents.
